Harold Wilson still offers
to help promote negotiations.

836
01:15:31,560 --> 01:15:33,471
That was all there was to it?

837
01:15:33,720 --> 01:15:36,234
Yes, he turned away...

838
01:15:37,840 --> 01:15:40,229
and left me bewildered.

839
01:15:44,320 --> 01:15:46,629
It was up to me to decide...

840
01:15:47,320 --> 01:15:51,029
when the imaginary character
had given way...

841
01:15:51,280 --> 01:15:54,875
to the real one
if there ever was a real one.

842
01:16:01,600 --> 01:16:04,034
I am Princess Aïcha Abadie,

843
01:16:04,280 --> 01:16:08,114
and in spite of my fragile,
doll-like appearance,

844
01:16:08,360 --> 01:16:10,999
I am a very strong-minded woman!

845
01:16:11,240 --> 01:16:14,755
I do not like people to resist me,
I want to be obeyed!

846
01:16:15,000 --> 01:16:16,115
Your orders, ma'am?

847
01:16:16,360 --> 01:16:17,998
I am Lebanese by adoption.

848
01:16:18,240 --> 01:16:22,677
In 1 960, I married the Emir Abadie,

849
01:16:22,920 --> 01:16:27,789
and I am Queen of Lebanon in exile,
for, as you know, my country...

850
01:16:28,040 --> 01:16:30,076
is now a Socialist Republic.

851
01:16:30,320 --> 01:16:32,709
I am therefore in Nice incognito,

852
01:16:32,960 --> 01:16:36,157
as my husband and l
have terrible enemies.

853
01:16:36,400 --> 01:16:39,631
There are prices on our heads
in Lebanon.

854
01:16:39,880 --> 01:16:43,714
I am often the target
of machine-gun fire...

855
01:16:43,960 --> 01:16:47,396
which always misses me,
no doubt because of Allah's protection.

856
01:16:47,640 --> 01:16:49,631
In order to marry the Emir,

857
01:16:49,880 --> 01:16:51,996
I had to convert to the Moslem faith.

858
01:16:52,240 --> 01:16:56,836
I have flown to Beyrouth twice
in my husband's space machine.

859
01:16:57,880 --> 01:17:01,077
Well, Alexis? Please keep me...

860
01:17:01,880 --> 01:17:06,556
from flying away, the sea is choppy,
and you know how light I am.

861
01:17:15,000 --> 01:17:17,434
Help me, Ferdinand.

862
01:17:27,080 --> 01:17:29,640
Ferdinand, we weigh anchor in an hour.

863
01:17:29,880 --> 01:17:30,596
Yes, Princess.

864
01:17:30,840 --> 01:17:33,434
Alexis, take me into town.

865
01:17:38,040 --> 01:17:39,189
Pierrot!

866
01:17:55,880 --> 01:17:57,108
It's me!

867
01:17:57,520 --> 01:18:00,512
My name's Ferdinand... Hi.

868
01:18:01,120 --> 01:18:04,032
You don't seem surprised to see me.

869
01:18:04,520 --> 01:18:06,238
How'd you get here?

870
01:18:06,480 --> 01:18:10,473
I'm so glad I've found you at last!

871
01:18:12,560 --> 01:18:15,632
- Where are you staying?
- With you, idiot!

872
01:18:15,880 --> 01:18:19,953
I'm staying with you.
I looked for you everywhere!

873
01:18:24,280 --> 01:18:25,952
Why didn't you wait for me?

874
01:18:27,120 --> 01:18:28,792
I wanted to...

875
01:18:29,280 --> 01:18:32,317
but I only just got away
before those men came.

876
01:18:32,560 --> 01:18:35,996
Then I ran to the dance-hall
to tell you not to come,

877
01:18:36,240 --> 01:18:38,196
but you weren't there,

878
01:18:38,560 --> 01:18:40,551
so I went back

879
01:18:40,800 --> 01:18:43,951
and I saw those other men
getting into the blue Ford.

880
01:18:44,200 --> 01:18:46,919
And I thought they'd killed you.

881
01:18:48,280 --> 01:18:51,670
So I went away... I didn't care where...

882
01:18:51,920 --> 01:18:56,436
I don't even remember where...
I was afraid to go back to the sea-shore.

883
01:18:57,400 --> 01:19:02,679
Then one day I ran into Fred in a bar.

884
01:19:02,920 --> 01:19:05,912
I swear I did!
The Las Vegas bar, in Toulon!

885
01:19:06,160 --> 01:19:09,470
- How'd you know I was here?
- By accident.

886
01:19:10,960 --> 01:19:12,712
It's the truth, you know...

887
01:19:14,920 --> 01:19:16,831
I believe you, liar...

888
01:19:17,080 --> 01:19:19,674
Why don't you ever believe I love you?

889
01:19:19,920 --> 01:19:21,990
I do love you... in my own way.

890
01:19:22,240 --> 01:19:23,832
That's true.

891
01:19:24,360 --> 01:19:25,634
I can prove it.

892
01:19:25,880 --> 01:19:30,112
Look... I went back to our beach
and got your notebook.

893
01:19:30,360 --> 01:19:31,713
Thanks.

894
01:19:32,160 --> 01:19:34,116
Look at the last page.

895
01:19:35,400 --> 01:19:38,631
There's a little poem about you.
I wrote it.

896
01:19:39,360 --> 01:19:41,749
"Tender... and cruel...

897
01:19:42,280 --> 01:19:45,272
Real... and surreal...

898
01:19:45,680 --> 01:19:48,319
Terrifying... and funny...

899
01:19:48,800 --> 01:19:51,519
Nocturnal and diurnal

900
01:19:51,920 --> 01:19:55,435
Toward and untoward

901
01:19:55,680 --> 01:19:57,591
- Handsome as anything
- Crazy Pierrot..."

902
01:19:57,840 --> 01:20:00,638
My name's Ferdinand!
I told you so before, God damn it!

903
01:20:00,880 --> 01:20:04,270
If you think it suits you to say
"God damn it"...

904
01:20:04,800 --> 01:20:06,233
God can go to...

905
01:20:06,480 --> 01:20:08,596
Don't talk like that.

906
01:20:09,040 --> 01:20:13,033
You can talk! We're wanted for murder!
You know what a murder is?

907
01:20:13,280 --> 01:20:16,750
Sure I know... So what?
Does it scare you?

908
01:20:18,360 --> 01:20:19,873
Well, answer me...

909
01:20:20,160 --> 01:20:23,869
I'm looking at you, I'm listening to you,
but that's not what counts.

910
01:20:24,120 --> 01:20:25,348
Well, thanks a lot!

911
01:20:25,600 --> 01:20:29,309
No... I mean right this moment,
but it's already gone...

912
01:20:29,560 --> 01:20:34,839
It's... oh, I don't know... the color
of the sky... our relationship...

913
01:20:35,080 --> 01:20:36,718
I don't get it.

914
01:20:38,120 --> 01:20:40,270
I wish time would stand still.

915
01:20:41,040 --> 01:20:43,349
Look... I put my hand on your knee.

916
01:20:44,520 --> 01:20:48,308
That's a wonderful thing in itself...
That's life.

917
01:20:48,680 --> 01:20:51,717
Space... feelings...

918
01:20:53,240 --> 01:20:57,233
Instead, I'm coming with you...
back to our tale of sound and fury.

919
01:20:57,560 --> 01:20:58,709
Actually, I don't care.

920
01:20:58,960 --> 01:21:00,552
Come on... Fred's waiting.

921
01:21:00,800 --> 01:21:03,758
OK, forget it... Let's go, daddy-o.

922
01:21:06,880 --> 01:21:10,077
I wonder what's keeping the cops.
We should be in jail by now.

923
01:21:10,320 --> 01:21:14,233
They're smart...
They let people destroy themselves.

924
01:21:41,600 --> 01:21:43,477
Why do you do things like that?

925
01:21:43,720 --> 01:21:47,156
But I tell you I didn't kill him!

926
01:22:02,800 --> 01:22:05,314
It's funny we've survived
all that killing.

927
01:22:05,560 --> 01:22:07,073
Yeah... funny... ha ha ha.

928
01:22:07,320 --> 01:22:08,799
Just like in Pepe-le-Moko.

929
01:22:09,040 --> 01:22:10,393
Who?

930
01:22:11,200 --> 01:22:13,270
- Pepe-le-Moko.
- Who's that?

931
01:22:13,520 --> 01:22:15,875
Wow! You really don't know much!

932
01:22:21,240 --> 01:22:23,708
What about you?
Do you know what you are?

933
01:22:23,960 --> 01:22:26,155
I am homosexualis.

934
01:22:26,840 --> 01:22:28,193
Says you!

935
01:22:28,880 --> 01:22:32,668
I know who you are...
But you don't know.

936
01:22:32,920 --> 01:22:38,597
That's true. I'm just a huge question mark
overlooking the Mediterranean.

937
01:22:54,680 --> 01:22:56,352
Are your parents still alive?

938
01:22:56,600 --> 01:22:59,751
Yes, and they've never been separated.

939
01:23:00,080 --> 01:23:02,514
Once, they were almost separated.

940
01:23:03,240 --> 01:23:06,073
Papa was taking a trip somewhere...

941
01:23:06,320 --> 01:23:08,276
A little trip.

942
01:23:08,960 --> 01:23:12,032
They didn't have enough money
for 2 tickets...

943
01:23:12,560 --> 01:23:15,279
Mama went with him to the bus-stop...

944
01:23:15,720 --> 01:23:17,551
And they looked at each other:

945
01:23:17,800 --> 01:23:21,156
papa in the window,
mama on the pavement.

946
01:23:22,000 --> 01:23:25,879
And just as the bus started,
papa got off in a hurry:

947
01:23:26,120 --> 01:23:28,190
he didn't want to leave mama.

948
01:23:28,440 --> 01:23:33,389
And while he was getting off in front,
she was getting on in back,

949
01:23:33,640 --> 01:23:35,756
because she didn't want to leave him.

950
01:23:36,000 --> 01:23:38,275
Finally, papa gave up his trip.

951
01:23:38,520 --> 01:23:41,159
What did you do in that shop?

952
01:23:41,400 --> 01:23:44,870
Oh, I watched people's faces.

953
01:23:45,120 --> 01:23:48,032
- Where was it?
- Galeries Lafayette.

954
01:23:49,800 --> 01:23:51,518
Why all these questions?

955
01:23:51,760 --> 01:23:53,671
I want to know exactly who you are.

956
01:23:53,920 --> 01:23:56,070
I never knew... Not even 5 years ago.

957
01:23:56,840 --> 01:24:00,389
Oh, I'm just a sentimental girl,
that's all.

958
01:24:01,080 --> 01:24:03,514
What a fool you are
to make a mystery of that!

959
01:24:03,760 --> 01:24:09,039
What's your brother do? I never know
when you're making things up!

960
01:24:09,920 --> 01:24:11,512
Oh... my brother...

961
01:24:11,760 --> 01:24:13,876
What was he doing in Tel Aviv?

962
01:24:16,520 --> 01:24:19,478
Listen... at the moment
there's a war in Yemen...

963
01:24:19,720 --> 01:24:22,154
You don't know anything!

964
01:24:22,760 --> 01:24:25,672
He gets money from the Royalists...

965
01:24:25,920 --> 01:24:28,957
What about those other men?
The Arab League?

966
01:24:29,200 --> 01:24:30,679
Who knows? Probably...

967
01:24:30,920 --> 01:24:33,150
Is there really a troop of dancers?

968
01:24:33,720 --> 01:24:35,278
What do you care?

969
01:24:35,520 --> 01:24:40,435
Why does he need a cover? Nowadays,
gun-running is practically official!

970
01:24:40,720 --> 01:24:43,234
- What do you care?
- Answer me!

971
01:24:43,480 --> 01:24:45,118
Listen:

972
01:24:46,240 --> 01:24:50,836
there are 3,600 seconds in an hour.

973
01:24:51,720 --> 01:24:55,759
That makes
about 1 00,000 seconds in a day.

974
01:24:56,640 --> 01:24:59,757
In an average lifetime, that makes...

975
01:25:01,160 --> 01:25:04,596
250 billion seconds!

976
01:25:05,600 --> 01:25:10,720
All in all, the two of us
have been together for a month.

977
01:25:11,360 --> 01:25:16,798
Add it all up! You'll find I've only been
with you a couple of million seconds...

978
01:25:17,040 --> 01:25:20,430
out of the 250 billion
that go to make up your life.

979
01:25:21,080 --> 01:25:25,039
That's not much...
So I'm not surprised that I don't know...

980
01:25:25,280 --> 01:25:27,191
who you are, either.

981
01:25:49,200 --> 01:25:52,112
- Is he willing?
- He'll do anything I want.

982
01:25:52,920 --> 01:25:55,036
What a crazy set-up!

983
01:26:25,680 --> 01:26:27,318
What am I supposed to do?

984
01:26:28,120 --> 01:26:29,758
You'll do as you're told.

985
01:26:30,000 --> 01:26:32,878
Just keep your eyes and ears open.

986
01:26:34,360 --> 01:26:36,715
Remember the scent of eucalyptus?

987
01:26:37,800 --> 01:26:40,758
- With you, it's always mixed up.
- No, everything is simple.

988
01:26:41,000 --> 01:26:42,069
Too much at once

989
01:26:42,320 --> 01:26:43,309
No...

990
01:26:43,560 --> 01:26:45,437
A little harbor, as in Conrad

991
01:26:45,680 --> 01:26:48,513
A sail-boat,
as in Robert Louis Stevenson

992
01:26:48,760 --> 01:26:51,149
An old brothel, as in Faulkner

993
01:26:51,400 --> 01:26:55,075
A steward-turned-millionaire,
as in Jack London

994
01:26:55,960 --> 01:26:58,713
- With you, it's always mixed up.
- Everything's simple.

995
01:26:58,960 --> 01:27:00,678
- Too much at once
- No...

996
01:27:00,920 --> 01:27:04,993
Two men who beat me up,
as in Raymond Chandler

997
01:27:05,240 --> 01:27:08,391
and you... and me... and him...
see how simple it is?

998
01:27:08,640 --> 01:27:09,709
I don't see at all.

999
01:27:09,960 --> 01:27:11,109
- They want to
- buy the yacht.

1000
01:27:11,360 --> 01:27:12,429
- The old man
- isn't French.

1001
01:27:12,680 --> 01:27:14,238
- My brother
- collects the money.

1002
01:27:14,480 --> 01:27:15,913
- The others
- don't know.

1003
01:27:16,160 --> 01:27:17,229
- They'll be
- furious.

1004
01:27:17,480 --> 01:27:19,596
They tail Fred...
we get rid of them.

1005
01:27:19,840 --> 01:27:21,751
- And then?
- You'll do as you're told!

1006
01:27:52,120 --> 01:27:53,997
It's easy for a girl
to kill a lot of people.

1007
01:27:54,240 --> 01:27:57,232
There's no reason
why soft breasts and thighs...

1008
01:27:57,480 --> 01:28:01,792
should keep her from killing everybody
to stay free or defend herself!

1009
01:28:02,040 --> 01:28:06,079
Just look at Cuba...
or Viet Nam... or Israel.

1010
01:28:20,560 --> 01:28:22,869
- I love you!
- Me too.

1011
01:29:28,800 --> 01:29:32,076
Next chapter: despair

1012
01:29:32,320 --> 01:29:36,677
Next chapter: freedom...
bitterness...

1013
01:29:56,280 --> 01:29:59,716
Seen a girl who looks
like a movie star?

1014
01:30:00,840 --> 01:30:02,512
None of your business.

1015
01:30:07,000 --> 01:30:08,752
- Is it all there?
- Yes...

1016
01:30:09,000 --> 01:30:12,356
- We all meet tonight as planned?
- Yes...

1017
01:30:16,640 --> 01:30:18,471
Some people saw me.

1018
01:30:19,480 --> 01:30:20,549
I don't understand.

1019
01:30:20,800 --> 01:30:22,995
That way, it'll look like Fred's
in the clear.

1020
01:30:23,240 --> 01:30:25,231
Why are you double-crossing me?

1021
01:30:28,680 --> 01:30:29,999
What's the matter?

1022
01:30:30,240 --> 01:30:33,835
Nothing... I'm looking
at a woman who's hurting me.

1023
01:30:34,080 --> 01:30:37,311
$50,000 would make anyone nervous,
Pierrot.

1024
01:30:37,560 --> 01:30:39,278
My name's Ferdinand.

1025
01:30:39,720 --> 01:30:41,312
Why did you kiss me just now?

1026
01:30:41,560 --> 01:30:43,551
Because I felt like it.

1027
01:30:46,080 --> 01:30:49,117
- Kiss me again.
- Not here.

1028
01:30:51,480 --> 01:30:53,755
Why do you wear such tight slacks?

1029
01:30:54,000 --> 01:30:58,437
If you don't like it,
go back to Paris.

1030
01:30:59,120 --> 01:31:00,678
Kiss me.

1031
01:31:01,120 --> 01:31:02,712
OK, I get it.

1032
01:31:03,200 --> 01:31:05,873
You know, it's not healthy
to double-cross us.

1033
01:31:06,120 --> 01:31:07,633
"Be quiet, Cassandra."

1034
01:31:07,880 --> 01:31:10,075
- What?
- It's the title of this book.

1035
01:31:10,320 --> 01:31:11,833
You poor idiot!

1036
01:31:14,760 --> 01:31:15,909
Listen...

1037
01:31:16,560 --> 01:31:18,312
- Marianne!
- What?

1038
01:31:18,560 --> 01:31:23,634
TWA - Nice airport - 2:45 PM plane for
Tahiti... We just have to climb aboard.

1039
01:31:24,440 --> 01:31:26,271
Just the two of us...

1040
01:31:26,520 --> 01:31:28,272
Obviously.

1041
01:31:34,720 --> 01:31:36,312
Obviously.

1042
01:31:37,000 --> 01:31:38,513
Words are funny...

1043
01:31:38,760 --> 01:31:41,718
They say the opposite of what they mean.

1044
01:31:41,960 --> 01:31:45,316
We say "obviously"
when things aren't obvious at all.

1045
01:31:45,560 --> 01:31:48,950
Like it wasn't obvious to me
that I'd find the old man...

1046
01:31:49,200 --> 01:31:52,078
with a bullet-hole in his forehead.

1047
01:31:52,640 --> 01:31:56,269
- Did you know your brother'd kill him?
- It was none of my business.

1048
01:31:56,520 --> 01:31:58,750
I'm willing to run away with you,

1049
01:31:59,000 --> 01:32:01,798
but Fred will find us and get even.

1050
01:32:02,040 --> 01:32:04,793
I saw him get even with a girl once.

1051
01:32:05,040 --> 01:32:06,758
I'll protect you.

1052
01:32:09,400 --> 01:32:12,437
OK. But I have to go alone
or they'll suspect.

1053
01:32:12,680 --> 01:32:13,908
OK, beautiful.

1054
01:32:14,160 --> 01:32:15,673
OK, handsome.

1055
01:32:18,800 --> 01:32:19,869
Well...

1056
01:32:20,440 --> 01:32:23,113
I'm off, since we've nothing more to say.

1057
01:32:23,360 --> 01:32:25,237
Meet me in half an hour.

1058
01:32:25,480 --> 01:32:26,708
No...

1059
01:32:27,240 --> 01:32:28,958
I'll count to...

1060
01:32:29,840 --> 01:32:31,432
1 37...

1061
01:32:33,040 --> 01:32:34,792
You're really crazy.

1062
01:32:39,920 --> 01:32:42,275
1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6...

1063
01:32:44,680 --> 01:32:46,159
What about the case?

1064
01:32:46,400 --> 01:32:50,359
Start the car. Trust me,
and I'll trust you. 1 8, 1 9, 20...

1065
01:33:50,160 --> 01:33:52,993
1 06, 1 07, 1 08, 1 09, 1 1 0...

1066
01:34:59,400 --> 01:35:00,879
Anything wrong?

1067
01:35:01,120 --> 01:35:03,714
It's... it's that tune.

1068
01:35:04,000 --> 01:35:06,195
You can't imagine
what it means to me.

1069
01:35:06,440 --> 01:35:07,793
That tune... hear it?

1070
01:35:08,040 --> 01:35:10,235
No, I don't hear a thing.

1071
01:35:11,000 --> 01:35:13,195
You wouldn't understand...

1072
01:35:13,440 --> 01:35:16,352
That tune's my whole life!

1073
01:35:16,800 --> 01:35:19,917
When I hear it...
it does something to me!

1074
01:35:20,160 --> 01:35:24,199
One day I was at home,
it was on the radio...

1075
01:35:28,000 --> 01:35:33,472
She was sitting beside me...
she was beautiful...

1076
01:35:35,360 --> 01:35:37,351
I took her hand, like this...

1077
01:35:37,600 --> 01:35:41,388
And I stroked the back of it,
like this...

1078
01:35:42,160 --> 01:35:46,199
I asked her: "Do... you... love... me?"

1079
01:35:48,920 --> 01:35:50,558
She said: "No!"

1080
01:35:52,400 --> 01:35:56,154
So I bought the record,
because that music got me!

1081
01:35:58,600 --> 01:36:01,433
A case of mass hysteria
all by myself!

1082
01:36:01,680 --> 01:36:05,912
One day, at home,
I put on the record...

1083
01:36:07,480 --> 01:36:12,713
It went round and round in my head!
Everything was spinning!

1084
01:36:13,480 --> 01:36:16,631
She was beside me...
Not the same woman, another one...

1085
01:36:16,880 --> 01:36:19,269
Not as pretty as the first...

1086
01:36:21,680 --> 01:36:23,159
But what can you do?

1087
01:36:23,760 --> 01:36:25,796
I took her hand...

1088
01:36:26,200 --> 01:36:31,433
and stroked it... on the other side,
this time... I wanted a change.

1089
01:36:32,200 --> 01:36:35,510
I asked her: "Do... you... Love... me?"

1090
01:36:38,640 --> 01:36:41,029
And she said: "Certainly".

1091
01:36:43,960 --> 01:36:47,748
But I didn't love her.
So I broke the record!

1092
01:36:50,640 --> 01:36:55,668
One day, I turned on the radio
and it was playing.

1093
01:36:55,920 --> 01:36:58,434
Why that? Why not something else?

1094
01:36:58,680 --> 01:37:02,673
She was beside me... on the other side:
it was her house.

1095
01:37:02,960 --> 01:37:04,951
Still another woman...

1096
01:37:05,840 --> 01:37:07,831
I took her hand

1097
01:37:08,080 --> 01:37:10,674
and stroked it. On both sides,
just to get it over with...

1098
01:37:10,920 --> 01:37:13,832
This thing was getting on my nerves!

1099
01:37:14,080 --> 01:37:17,072
I asked her: "Do... you... Love... me?"

1100
01:37:18,920 --> 01:37:20,956
She said: "Yes, sir."

1101
01:37:23,040 --> 01:37:25,679
I asked her:
"Will you give me your hand?"

1102
01:37:25,920 --> 01:37:28,639
She said:
"You've had it for ten minutes."

1103
01:37:28,880 --> 01:37:31,348
She was right...
"You're right," I said.

1104
01:37:33,240 --> 01:37:34,832
So I kept it.

1105
01:37:38,560 --> 01:37:42,758
I kept it ten years!
I can't stand that tune any more!

1106
01:37:43,000 --> 01:37:47,312
Do you hear it?
I can't stand it any more! Hear it?

1107
01:37:47,560 --> 01:37:48,709
No.

1108
01:37:49,120 --> 01:37:51,634
That one, right there...
You can't hear it?

1109
01:37:51,880 --> 01:37:53,359
No.

1110
01:37:54,040 --> 01:37:56,554
Tell me... am I crazy?

1111
01:37:56,800 --> 01:37:58,153
Come right out and say it!

1112
01:37:58,400 --> 01:38:02,075
I'd like to hear you say it...
Say: "You're crazy!"

1113
01:38:02,320 --> 01:38:05,392
- You're crazy.
- Well, that's more like it.

1114
01:38:14,360 --> 01:38:16,271
- Going to the island?
- Yes, sir.

1115
01:38:16,520 --> 01:38:19,114
- What's your boat called?
- Howa.

1116
01:38:20,160 --> 01:38:22,469
"Howa you"!

1117
01:38:32,640 --> 01:38:35,552
Then that tune I hear
doesn't exist?

1118
01:38:36,600 --> 01:38:39,273
The tune I've been hearing all my life?

1119
01:38:39,520 --> 01:38:42,114
That tenderness?
No! Insensitive man!

1120
01:38:43,720 --> 01:38:46,029
You missed the whole point!

1121
01:39:10,000 --> 01:39:12,230
Do you love me?

1122
01:39:58,520 --> 01:40:01,796
I held her close and began to cry.

1123
01:40:02,320 --> 01:40:05,835
It was our first, our only dream.

1124
01:40:28,240 --> 01:40:30,470
I want to make a call to Paris.

1125
01:40:31,160 --> 01:40:33,594
Balzac 75-02.

1126
01:40:34,680 --> 01:40:37,433
So you've forgotten Balzac, too?

1127
01:40:38,280 --> 01:40:39,952
Yes... I'll wait.

1128
01:40:48,840 --> 01:40:50,319
It hurts.

1129
01:40:53,400 --> 01:40:55,470
You brought it on yourself.

1130
01:41:07,920 --> 01:41:09,911
You brought it on yourself.

1131
01:41:14,240 --> 01:41:16,913
Please forgive me, Pierrot...

1132
01:41:17,520 --> 01:41:19,158
My name's Ferdinand.

1133
01:41:19,600 --> 01:41:21,318
It's too late.

1134
01:41:46,720 --> 01:41:48,915
Yes... I'm waiting.

1135
01:42:01,120 --> 01:42:03,588
Balzac 75-02?

1136
01:42:04,320 --> 01:42:06,436
Is Mrs. Griffon there?

1137
01:42:08,360 --> 01:42:09,588
Who is this?

1138
01:42:10,240 --> 01:42:11,593
The maid?

1139
01:42:13,040 --> 01:42:14,837
How are the children?

1140
01:42:16,560 --> 01:42:18,710
Nobody's calling!

1141
01:42:26,240 --> 01:42:27,559
death

1142
01:43:01,640 --> 01:43:04,552
... what I wanted to say...

1143
01:43:08,440 --> 01:43:09,873
Why?

1144
01:44:08,440 --> 01:44:09,270
This is silly...

1145
01:44:49,800 --> 01:44:51,358
- It's ours again
- What is?

1146
01:44:51,600 --> 01:44:53,670
- Eternity
- No, that's just the sea

1147
01:44:53,920 --> 01:44:55,558
And the sun

1148
01:44:58,680 --> 01:45:02,639
Remerciements au ministère
des affaires étrangères.
